Package: gspy
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Suggests: linux-perf
Description: forensic goroutine-to-syscall inspector for live Go processes
 gspy attaches to a running Go process and displays a live map of goroutine
 IDs to kernel syscalls using eBPF uprobes and tracepoints. Designed for
 security incident response and forensic analysis of Go-based processes.
 .
 No instrumentation, no recompilation, no process restart, and no
 modification of the target binary's memory or hash is required.
 Goroutine IDs are extracted from thread-local storage via process_vm_readv.
 .
 Requires Linux kernel 5.8+ with CONFIG_BPF_SYSCALL=y and
 CAP_BPF + CAP_PERFMON capabilities (or CAP_SYS_ADMIN).
